Biography
Sunil Yadav
Competent software professional with over 13 years of cross-functional experience in scrum, managing international processes. Extensive experience of 4 years working in an Agile development environment .
My responsibilities include:
• Implementing agile SCRUM and XP practices in projects as Agile Coach/SCRUM Master.Facilitating Daily scrum meetings, sprint planning, sprint review, and sprint retrospective.
• Managing projects in both Agile and Waterfall development environments.Knowledge and experience with widely successful agile techniques: User Stories, TDD, Continuous Integration, Continuous Testing, Pairing, Automated Testing, Agile Games etc.
• Responsible for monitoring and maintaining quality and compliance targets.Good Experience of Agile approaches: SCRUM, XP, Kanban, SAFe, LeSS, etcExperience applying a wide variety of well documented patterns and techniques for filling in the intentional gaps left in the Scrum approach (for example: numerous Burndown techniques, numerous Retrospective formats, dependency management etc)
• Monitoring and auditing of products to ensure high standards of quality.
• Training/Support on agile practices and support for implementing JIRA tool for agile practice management




Work experience
Samsung Research Institute Delhi, Lead EngineerJuly 2011 - Present, Noida, Uttar Pradesh, IndiaKey Responsibility Areas
	SCRUM Master/Agile Coach
•	Implementing agile SCRUM and XP practices in projects as Agile Coach/SCRUM Master.
•	Manage and facilitate Agile/Scrum practices and disciplines in cross-functional Scrum Teams - including Daily Standups, Retrospective Meetings and Sprint Planning, etc.
•	Provide guidance and coaching to Scrum Teams on how to use Agile/Scrum practices and ensure the teams are practicing the core agile principles 
•	Identify and provide ideas to correct gaps in Agile/Scrum practices and improve delivery of projects.
•	Coach, mentor, teach, refresh agile scrum practices (roles, process, artifacts) as needed among program teams
•	Create training materials relative to specific agile training needs and conduct the training
•	Agile tool JIRA configuration and training for new programs implementing Agile Scrum, Kanban
•	Participate in enterprise agile transformation team efforts
•	Work closely with Agile Enablement team at HQ on priorities, lessons learned and overall agile transformation

Highlights: 
•	Good Experience of Agile approaches: SCRUM, XP, Kanban, SAFe, LeSS, etc  
•	Knowledge and experience with widely successful agile techniques: User Stories, TDD, Continuous Integration, Continuous Testing, Pairing, Automated Testing, Agile Games etc.
•	Experience applying a wide variety of well documented patterns and techniques for filling in the intentional gaps left in the Scrum approach (for example: numerous Burndown techniques, numerous Retrospective formats, dependency management etc)
•	Excellent communication and mentoring skills
	
	SEPG Member and KPI Mgt.
•	Process definition, improvement, update, release, implementation support
•	Performing internal audits and project reviews
•	SE Portal requirements gathering and implementation across organization
•	Design and upkeep QMS as per Samsung Assessment Modal similar to CMMI 
•	Project artifacts reviews, audits, project monitoring and reporting issues.
•	KPI automation, management, analysis and reporting
•	CAPA, 5 Why analysis implementation ,Root cause analysis meeting and action item tracking
•	Conducting Defect Prevention Meetings and Publishing Process Capability Baselines.
•	SE point of contact with HQ for process activities
Sony India Software Center, ConsultantSeptember 2009 - July 2011, Bangalore, Karnataka, IndiaKey Responsibility Areas
	Agile Consultant
•	Help project teams to adopt and improve Agile methods and practices
•	Moderating standup meetings, planning meetings and retrospectives in transitioning new projects from waterfall to Agile.	
